gov.nasa.jpf

Class ConsoleOutputStream

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.io.OutputStream
      • java.io.FilterOutputStream
        • java.io.PrintStream
          • gov.nasa.jpf.ConsoleOutputStream
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Closeable, Flushable, Appendable, AutoCloseable

    public class ConsoleOutputStream
extends PrintStream
    this is what we use for System.out and System.err, hence we go native as quickly as possible, hence we don't need an underlying stream. It's already slow enough as it is NOTE - we have to intercept *everything* that might go to our base class, since it is not initialized properly (we want to avoid costly PrinStream init unless we really need it
